---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Children & Teens – Cara Colgate, LICSW" currentPage="children">
  <div class="page-intro">
    <div class="intro-text">
      <p>
        Are you concerned about your child? Do they need support because of a
        loss, family or school issue, challenging emotions or learning
        difficulties?
      </p>
      <p>
        Working with children and families over the last 20 years has given me
        an in-depth understanding of child and adolescent development. It can be
        daunting to figure out why your child or teen is having challenges and
        what kind of support they need. My role is to help them gain resilience
        and skills to navigate their world, and to help you more effectively
        support your child.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img
      src="/images/children-hands.jpg"
      alt="Adult and child hands held together"
      class="page-image"
    />
  </div>

  <p>
    With younger children, I rely on play therapy and cognitive behavioral
    therapy (CBT) in my work to help build coping skills, empathy, and better
    social skills for children in a developmentally-appropriate manner. Play is
    the primary language for children, so I encourage children to express and
    explore thoughts and feelings through various forms of play including sand
    tray and art therapy. I also use CBT to teach skills that can be utilized
    outside of our sessions, helping children recognize their own emotions,
    notice and critically evaluate their thoughts, and use adaptive behavioral
    strategies, mindfulness, and other self-soothing techniques to remain
    grounded in difficult situations or when having big emotions.
  </p>

  <p>
    With adolescents, I focus on CBT, expressive and talk therapy. Therapy
    reinforces the message that your child's thoughts and feelings are
    important, and that talking about issues and thoughtful problem solving are
    important life tools. Young people also often appreciate the chance to
    explore their relationships, goals and perspectives with an adult outside
    their family.
  </p>

  <p>
    Effective child and adolescent therapy relies on your involvement, so my
    goal is to partner with you to support your child. Collaboration with
    teachers and other adults can also have a profound impact, so I encourage
    phone or in-person consultations when appropriate.
  </p>

  <p>
    It's important that you find a therapist who is the right fit for your
    child. I'm glad to answer any questions you have about my practice, therapy
    or how to find help. Please{" "}
    <a href="/connect/">contact me</a> to set up an introductory phone call.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-intro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 220px;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .intro-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .page-image {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1.3rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .page-intro {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .page-image {
      max-width: 260px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }
</style>
